MSTest v4 **removed `[ExpectedException]`**. The replacement is **`Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()`** — you move the assertion inline into the test body:

```csharp
// Before (v3):
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After (v4):
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

For **async** methods, use `Assert.ThrowsExactlyAsync<T>()`.

Use `Assert.Throws<T>()` / `Assert.ThrowsAsync<T>()` instead if you want to also match **derived** exception types (like `[ExpectedException]` did).

